        "BLOOM Charity's operational model is distinguished by its direct provision of services, which results in a <cite id=\"12\">cost per beneficiary of approximately $6.80</cite>. This high-impact, low-cost approach is coupled with a <cite id=\"13\">Platinum Seal of Transparency from Candid</cite>, the highest level of disclosure available. Their impact is tangible, with <cite id=\"14\">120 children gaining access</cite> to new PlayGardens in Fes and Errachidia in a single reporting cycle, demonstrating a clear theory of change that links specialized play environments to improved childhood outcomes."
      ],
      "summary": "BLOOM Charity is a specialized non-profit organization that <cite id=\"1\">empowers vulnerable children through play environments</cite> and crisis mobilization. Since its <cite id=\"2\">founding in 2017</cite>, the organization has focused on the developmental needs of orphans and at-risk youth, particularly in Morocco and crisis zones like Gaza. The charity operates with exceptional financial leaness, reporting <cite id=\"3\">total revenue of $158,297</cite> in 2023 while maintaining a <cite id=\"4\">program expense ratio of 98.7%</cite>. This fiscal efficiency is further evidenced by its <cite id=\"5\">fundraising efficiency of $0.03 per $1 raised</cite>, ensuring that nearly every dollar contributed directly reaches beneficiaries. BLOOM's primary interventions include the construction of 'PlayGardens'\u2014specialized outdoor spaces designed for healing and development. By 2024, the organization had <cite id=\"6\">built 11 PlayGardens</cite> and significantly expanded its humanitarian reach, providing <cite id=\"7\">700,000 meals in Gaza</cite> during crisis periods. The organization is <cite id=\"8\">zakat-eligible</cite>, allowing Muslim donors to fulfill their religious obligations through programs that serve the <cite id=\"9\">masakin (needy)</cite> and vulnerable children in Muslim-majority regions.",
